<appendix id="app.markup">
    <title>Markup Conventions</title>
    <para>Refer to Norman Walsh's DocBook Guide,
      <ulink url="http://www.docbook.org/tdg/en/html/docbook.html"/>,
      in case of further open questions about markup.
    </para>

    <sect1 id="sec.markup.conv">
      <title>Use of Identifiers</title>
      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>
      Always use an <sgmltag class="attribute">id</sgmltag> attribute in parts,
      chapters, appendixes, sections, figures, and examples. They are often used
      in other elements as well, such as tables and procedures.
     </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
      Only use ASCII characters in IDs to avoid processing problems.
     </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
      Insert a prefix. This prefix is determined by the element to which the
      <sgmltag class="attribute">id</sgmltag> attribute belongs. See
      <xref linkend="tab.abbreviations"/>.
     </para>
