        <listitem>
          <para>
      Identify a chapter with short, easy-to-remember English labels, like
      <sgmltag class="attvalue">inst_yast</sgmltag> for a chapter or section
      about YaST installation.
     </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
      Each section inherits the label of its parent plus a unique part that
      characterizes it. For example: <literal>sec.inst_yast</literal> might
      have a subsection labeled <literal>sec.inst_yast.lang</literal>. Other
      elements with IDs inherit the ID of the parent chapter. For example, a
      table in this chapter about foo could have the ID
      <literal>tab.inst_yast.foo</literal>.
     </para>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
      Separate the prefix and the following parts with a dot
      (<literal>.</literal>). Do not use colons (<literal>:</literal>),
      semicolons (<literal>;</literal>), or other <quote>special
      characters.</quote> The underbar (<literal>_</literal>) character is
      allowed.
     </para>
          <example>
            <title>Typical Examples of <sgmltag class="attribute">id</sgmltag>
              Values
            </title>
            <screen>id="sec.yast.installation"
id="cha.yast"
id="tab.yast.sources"</screen>
          </example>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </sect1>
